javax.portlet.annotations

Annotation Type Supports


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=ANNOTATION_TYPE)
public @interface Supports
    This annotation is used within composite portlet configuration annotations to specify the supported portlet modes and window states for a given locale. It cannot be used as a stand-alone portlet annotation.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String mimeType
      The MIME type for the supported portlet modes and window states listed in this annotation, for example "text/html".
      String[] portletModes
      The names of the supported portlet modes.
      String[] windowStates
      The names of the supported window states.

    • Element Detail

      • mimeType

        public abstract String mimeType
        The MIME type for the supported portlet modes and window states listed in this annotation, for example "text/html".

        The MIME type may also contain the wildcard character '*', for example "text/*" or "*/*".

        Returns:
        The mime type
        Default:
        "text/html"

      • portletModes

        public abstract String[] portletModes
        The names of the supported portlet modes.
        Returns:
        The supported portlet modes
        Default:
        ""

      • windowStates

        public abstract String[] windowStates
        The names of the supported window states.
        Returns:
        The supported window states
        Default:
        ""
